<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_MAP_FLAG">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies how the CPU should respond when an application calls the <see cref="ID3D11DeviceContext.Map" /> method on a resource that is being used by the GPU.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This enumeration is used by <see cref="ID3D11DeviceContext.Map" />.</para>
      <para>D3D11_MAP_FLAG_DO_NOT_WAIT cannot be used with <see cref="D3D11_MAP_WRITE_DISCARD" /> or <see cref="D3D11_MAP_WRITE_NOOVERWRITE" />.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-resource-enums">Resource Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_MAP_FLAG.D3D11_MAP_FLAG_DO_NOT_WAIT">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies that <see cref="ID3D11DeviceContext.Map" /> should return DXGI_ERROR_WAS_STILL_DRAWING when the GPU blocks the CPU from accessing a resource. For more information about this error code, see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3ddxgi/dxgi-error">DXGI_ERROR</a>.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>